
[1]peon

   PE'ON, n. In Hindoostan, a foot soldier, or a footman armed with sword
   and target; said to be corrupted from piadah. [Qu. L. pes, pedis.]
   Hence,

   1. In France, a common man in chess; usually written and called pawn.
